Day 6 â€“ HTML Tables

Tables display data in rows and columns.
Tags used: <table>, <tr>, <th>, <td>.
<th> defines heading cells and <td> defines normal data cells.
Example:

<table border="1">
  <tr><th>Name</th><th>Marks</th></tr>
  <tr><td>John</td><td>90</td></tr>
</table>


You can also merge cells using colspan or rowspan.
